## RubyMine
- start test
  command + shift + r start 
  P.S: command line: ruby -I some_test
- break point + debug mode
  command + shift + d: debug
  can also evaluate expressions
  - right click a break point to set conditions(e.g. break if satifies some condition)
- search
  command + shift
- Fuzzy search
  command + shift + T: sysmbol-search
  command + T: file-name-search
  
- Go To definition: command + click
- VCS features
- Control + option + T (or navigate/test): go to test file
- Refactor
  e.g. rename
- Command shift E: jump to recently added files
- control g: highlight occurrences ? seems incorrect
- ctrl w: 
